<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,1009,1756]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1009,1035]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Additional dorsocentral setae on presutural area present (
<figureCitation box="[899,999,1009,1035]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-110@37.[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 24. Colocasiomyia sabahana Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from the Park Headquarters area, Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia; C,E,G,K,M,O,Q) and C. sarawakana Toda &amp; Yafuso, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766454/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 24B</figureCitation>
).A pair of processes on male abdominal sternite VI nearly straight (
<figureCitation box="[444,538,1045,1071]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-18@13.[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male abdominal sternite VIs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (B in anteroventral view, C in lateral view), C. stamenicola (Carson &amp; Okada) (D in anterior view) and all species of the C. cristata subgroup (A in ventral view, E‒R in anterior view): A, C. ecornuta sp. nov.; E, C. grandis sp. nov.; F, C. vieti sp. nov.; G, C. cristata de Meijere; H, C. matthewsi sp. nov.; I, C. sulawesiana Okada &amp; Yafuso; J, C. kinabaluana sp. nov.; K, C. kotana sp. nov.; L, C. sabahana sp. nov.; M, C. sarawakana sp. nov.; N, C. pistilicola (Carson &amp; Okada); O, C. xenalocasiae (Okada); P, C. diconica (Toda &amp; Okada); Q, C. sumatrana sp. nov.; and R, C. leucocasiae sp. nov. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766420/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 9M</figureCitation>
). Epandrium roundish on posteroventral margin; anteroventral elongation broader than cercus in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[455,559,1081,1107]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-110@37.[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 24. Colocasiomyia sabahana Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from the Park Headquarters area, Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia; C,E,G,K,M,O,Q) and C. sarawakana Toda &amp; Yafuso, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766454/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 24H</figureCitation>
). Female abdominal sternite VI longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[1113,1211,1081,1107]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-110@37.[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 24. Colocasiomyia sabahana Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from the Park Headquarters area, Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia; C,E,G,K,M,O,Q) and C. sarawakana Toda &amp; Yafuso, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766454/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 24F</figureCitation>
). Oviscapt narrower than hypoproct, apically somewhat pointed in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[817,919,1117,1143]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-110@37.[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 24. Colocasiomyia sabahana Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from the Park Headquarters area, Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia; C,E,G,K,M,O,Q) and C. sarawakana Toda &amp; Yafuso, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766454/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 24L</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,1009,1756]" box="[199,1119,1153,1180]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1153,1179]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Description</emphasis>
(
<specimenCount box="[353,374,1153,1179]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[429,449,1154,1180]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
). Head. Supralateral setae outside prementum 3–4 per side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,1009,1756]" box="[199,1145,1189,1216]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Thorax. Basal scutellar setae long; posterior tip beyond half of apical scutellar setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,1009,1756]" box="[199,690,1225,1252]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Legs. Mid tibia with 2–3 apical, stout setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,1009,1756]" box="[199,842,1261,1288]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
Abdomen. Female sternite IV wider than long (
<figureCitation box="[730,830,1261,1287]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-110@37.[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 24. Colocasiomyia sabahana Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from the Park Headquarters area, Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia; C,E,G,K,M,O,Q) and C. sarawakana Toda &amp; Yafuso, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766454/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 24F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,1009,1756]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
Male terminalia. Epandrium with 9–10 setae on posteroventral portion (
<figureCitation box="[989,1092,1297,1323]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-110@37.[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 24. Colocasiomyia sabahana Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from the Park Headquarters area, Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia; C,E,G,K,M,O,Q) and C. sarawakana Toda &amp; Yafuso, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766454/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 24H</figureCitation>
). Median piece of subepandrial sclerite broad, somewhat quadrate plate; lateral pieces absent. Cercus with 37–38 setae, extended below, apically forming somewhat broad lobe with many small setae (
<figureCitation box="[760,865,1369,1395]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-110@37.[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 24. Colocasiomyia sabahana Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from the Park Headquarters area, Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia; C,E,G,K,M,O,Q) and C. sarawakana Toda &amp; Yafuso, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766454/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 24H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,1009,1756]" box="[199,1033,1405,1431]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
Female terminalia. Oviscapt with approximately 12 ovisensilla (
<figureCitation box="[918,1020,1405,1431]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-110@37.[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 24. Colocasiomyia sabahana Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from the Park Headquarters area, Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia; C,E,G,K,M,O,Q) and C. sarawakana Toda &amp; Yafuso, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766454/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 24L</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,1009,1756]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
Indices (range of 
<specimenCount box="[393,442,1441,1467]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="male">10♂</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[495,546,1441,1467]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="female">10♀</specimenCount>
